-- Wulff Says Immigrants `Belong in Our Country' in Turkish Assembly Address
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2010-10-19T12:20:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/wulff-says-immigrants-belong-in-our-country-in-turkish-assembly-address.html
German President Christian Wulff
said Turkish immigrants in Germany “belong in our country” and
urged them to integrate into society. Wulff, who has set off
domestic debate by saying Islam has a place among religions in
Germany, commented in a speech to the Turkish parliament today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tony Czuczka at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net  